All three reviewers converged on PASS/LGTM. Wrapper-level `commit=True` hoist is tighter than the originally-framed "13 callsites" fix.

## What Shipped
- **Schema:** 4 nullable TEXT columns added to `signal_events` (field, old_value, new_value, source_msg_id) via idempotent ALTER TABLE on 0-row table
- **Root-cause fix:** `_log_event()` wrappers now call `es.log(..., commit=True)` at the wrapper layer, covering all 11 emit sites (5 in micro-gate, 6 in oink-sync lifecycle) — self-committing event writes prevent the "dangling txn" zero-event bug
- **LIFECYCLE_EVENTS parity:** 19 event types in both canonical (`scripts/event_store.py`) and vendored (`oink_sync/event_store.py`) copies including PRICE_ALERT
- **Non-fatal wrapper:** try/except scope tight — wraps only event INSERT, never lifecycle UPDATE
- **Tests:** 19 new tests (11 event_store + 8 lifecycle), all pass; A3 regression and yfinance afterhours suites also green

